14 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
15 SECTION 1. AMENDATORY 43 O.S. 2021, Section 105, is
16 amended to read as follows:
17 Section 105. A. A proceeding for dissolution of marriage, an
18 annulment of a marriage, or a legal separation shall be titled "In
19 re the Marriage of _______ and ______".
20 B. The initial pleading in all proceedings under this title
21 shall be denominated a petition. The person filing the petition
22 shall be called the petitioner. A responsive pleading shall be
23 denominated a response. The person filing the responsive pleading
24 shall be called the respondent. Other pleadings shall be
Req. No. 12440 Page 1

1 deno minated as provided in the Rules of Civil Procedure, except as
2 otherwise provided in this section.
3 C. The petition must be verified as true, by the affidavit of
4 the petitioner.
5 D. A summons may issue thereon, and shall be served, or
6 publication made, as in other civil cases.
7 E. Wherever it occurs in this title or in any other title of
8 the Oklahoma Statutes or in any forms or court documents prepared
9 pursuant to the provisions of the Oklahoma Statutes, the term
10 "divorce" shall mean and be deemed to refer to a "dissolution of
11 marriage" unless the context or subject matter otherwise requires.
12 F. Standard forms sufficient to meet the statutory requirements
13 of this section and any other relevant sections in this title to
14 complete a divorce proceeding shall be prescribed by the Oklahoma
15 Bar Association in plain and understandable language, where
16 possible. The Administrative Office of the Courts shall provide
17 public access to the forms by providing a link on the Oklahoma State
18 Courts Network. Such standardized forms shall not be required to be
19 used in any proceeding.
20 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective November 1, 2025.
